						<summary>

						<p>MADRAS.</p>						

						<p>On a stone set up at the entrance into the Government Museum.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">ŚrI-Vīra-VegkaTapatirāyadēva-mahārāyar Śaka 153[.]</hi><note n="522-2">Though in the published text, the Śaka date has been read as 1530, it is possible to read it as 1531, which corresponded to the cyclic year Saumya quoted.</note><hi rend="bold">Saumya, Ṛishabha, Ēkādaśi, Friday, Rēvati = 1609 A.D., May 19. the tithi was ba. 11.</hi></p>						

						<p>Same as 294 of 1895.<note n="522-3">The text as published can be improved as follows: Line 12 <ta>lat tāriyatapār tevama</ta> ḷine 13 <ta>ṇyala kiṟā[ma]māṉa poḻica</ta> ḷine 16 <ta>ṉaviyappar akuroyicupara u-</ta> ḷine 25 <hi rend="grantha">kk</hi><ta>u vaṭa</ta><hi rend="grantha">kk</hi><ta>u tevikolla</ta> ḷine 26 <ta>yum cuṟṟupura[t]tu meṭum ku-</ta></note>Published in SII, V. Nos. 858.</p>						

